<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MONTEREY PARK; GRANT TO ALLOW POLICE TO BUY RADAR UNITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Police Department was recently awarded an $18,425 grant from the 
California Office of Traffic Safety. 
</P>
<P>
 The money will be used to purchase eight hand-held radar devices for the 
department's traffic bureau. Two of the devices will be used by the 
department's patrol force at targeted locations with speed problems.  
</P>
<P>
 The department applied for the grant in April and was required to submit a 
proposal outlining how the money would be used. 
</P>
