COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; SHELTER SEEKS NEW EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Union Station homeless shelter is seeking a new executive director to 
replace Gloria M. Kunkel, who will leave in January. 
</P>
<P>
 Kunkel said she wants to spend more time with her family. 
</P>
<P>
 A Union Station search committee is looking for a director who has a strong 
background in not-for-profit management and programs for the homeless. The 
director's responsibilities include supervising a 20-person staff, public 
relations, development and working with local agencies. The annual salary is 
about $50,000. 
