 * Huffington states that among his motives for wanting to become a senator is 
a desire to "give something back" (interview, Opinion, Oct. 30). May I suggest 
that the state of California would be better served were Huffington to do so on 
a graffiti cleanup team, or by volunteering in an elementary school populated 
by the children of working-poor immigrants, legal or otherwise. If only 
Huffington had taken the $27 million he's spent so far on his campaign and 
donated it for education, or medical care for the poor. That would be giving 
something back. If it turns out that this neophyte, know-nothing, rich boy is 
