<HEADLINE>
<P>
ITALY SUSPECTS MAY HAVE SHOT AT WRONG CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men arrested for the fatal shooting of a 7-year-old California boy may 
have mistaken the family's car for one transporting jewels, news reports said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 An anonymous source told police he had revealed to one of the suspects that a 
car similar to the one rented by the parents of Nicholas Green regularly 
carried jewels to stores in the area where he was shot, the reports said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects were arrested Tuesday. The Italian news agency ANSA identified 
them as Michele Iannello, 26, and Francesco Mesiano, 21, both of Vibo Valentia. 
</P>
<P>
 The Greens were driving through Calabria on the way to Sicily when robbers 
fired at their car Sept. 29. Nicholas, asleep in the back seat, was struck in 
the head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
