<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MALIBU; GOURMET FEAST TO RAISE FUNDS FOR FIRE VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Artists, writers, restaurateurs, culinary gurus and gastronomes are planning a 
fund-raiser Sunday for a group serving victims of last year's firestorm. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from the "Sunset Celebration," featuring live jazz and foods from 
well-known restaurants, will go to Operation Recovery, a group that formed 
within weeks of the fire to assist residents whose homes burned down. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration will be held at the home of artist Arlene Waxman, who has 
installed a monumental sculpture using debris from the fire. 
</P>
<P>
 The $50-a-person feast will feature food from restaurants such as Wolfgang 
Puck's Granita and Alice's, both in Malibu, and Michael's in Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 Collaborating in the effort is Cathy Rogers, a cooking instructor who has 
compiled a cookbook of family recipes from fire victims, with vignettes about 
why the dishes are significant to them. Priced at $19.95, the cookbook is to be 
released at the end of this month, with proceeds going to Operation Recovery. 
</P>
<P>
 To make reservations for "Sunset Celebration," call Ruth Rubenstein at (310) 
456-2348. The event is to be held at 29377 Cliffside Drive in the Point Dume 
community of Malibu. KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
