<HEADLINE>
<P>
RATS DEVOUR RUSSIAN WOMAN'S STASH OF CASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An elderly villager lost nearly all her savings when rats ate the cash she had 
hoarded in the basement of her house. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman, living alone in a village 80 miles east of Moscow, earns her living 
by making moonshine, the daily Komsomolskaya Pravda reported Wednesday, and had 
saved a million rubles, equivalent to $300. 
</P>
<P>
 "Having studied a variety of Russian state and commercial banks, the lady 
concluded that the safest place was her cellar," the paper said. It did not 
identify her further. 
</P>
<P>
 Many Russians prefer to keep their savings at home, since Russian banks offer 
interest rates lower than the high inflation rate and deposits are not 
considered safe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
