<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; STATE 800 
NUMBER SET UP TO REPORT VOTING FRAUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recent reports of alleged fraudulent voter registrations in the Southland have 
prompted state Atty. Gen. Dan Lungren to set up a statewide 800 telephone 
number, hoping to help citizens report illegal voting activities. 
</P>
<P>
 The (800) FRAUD98 hot line will operate 24 hours a day. It will remain in use 
during business hours for two weeks after next Tuesday's election. 
</P>
<P>
 Lungren said that with the election a week away, he hopes the hot line will 
act as a deterrent against people who want to tamper with the democratic 
process. Examples of voter fraud Lungren cited included voters who are 
underage, non-citizens and people registered to vote more than once. 
</P>
</TEXT>
