<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN FATALLY SHOT IN VAN NUYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old man who had recently moved to Panorama City was fatally wounded 
by gunfire as he walked to a friend's house late Tuesday, hours before he was 
about to start a new job at a bakery, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Miguel Huezo was apparently shot several times in the upper torso by a robber, 
Los Angeles Police Detective Stephen Fisk said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 10:45 p.m. outside an apartment complex in the 
8500 block of Cedros Avenue, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Huezo, originally from El Salvador, had recently moved to the San Fernando 
Valley from San Francisco and "was on his way to a new job when the incident 
took place," Fisk said. "Physical evidence indicates there was a struggle prior 
to the shooting." 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics rushed Huezo to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills, where 
he died shortly afterward, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
