SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; SUSPECT QUESTIONED IN MAN'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 38-year-old man was shot to death Wednesday in a residential neighborhood 
near Lake Los Angeles Park, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was shot several times in front of a house in the 17600 block of East 
Highacres Avenue about 4:30 p.m., according to Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Deputy Brian Jones. He died half an hour later at Antelope Valley Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators were questioning a suspect at the Antelope Valley sheriff's 
station in connection with the shooting but would not reveal any other 
information, Jones said. 
</P>
