<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MEN SOUGHT IN FIRES AT VACANT SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PHIL SNEIDERMAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are looking for several men, possibly transients, suspected 
of setting six fires in vacant Palmdale businesses and houses on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured, and little property damage was reported, Sgt. Bob Denham 
said.The motive for the fires was not immediately determined, and investigators 
were seeking the public's help in identifying and locating an unknown number of 
men seen running from the blazes set throughout the day. 
</P>
<P>
 "These were all abandoned structures," Denham said. "In several of those 
places, there was evidence that transients had been living there." 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses reported seeing men running from the scene of several of the fires, 
but descriptions were sketchy. The fires occurred mainly in Palmdale's former 
business district, near Sierra Highway. 
</P>
