<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWICE THE VICE FINDS SANTA ANITA THRICE NICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All Twice The Vice needed was a return to a track she likes. 
</P>
<P>
 After racing on soft turf at Belmont Park and a track at Keeneland that 
promoted speed horses in her two previous starts, Twice The Vice rebounded in a 
big way Wednesday at Santa Anita, pulling away through the stretch under Eddie 
Delahoussaye and beating Malli Star by five lengths in the $101,150 Linda Vista 
Breeders' Cup Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
 A winner of five of eight starts overall, Twice The Vice is now perfect in 
three starts at Santa Anita. She picked up $61,150 Wednesday for owners Bob and 
Beverly Lewis and covered the 1 1/16 miles in 1:41 2/5. She paid $9.40 as the 
7-2 second choice. 
</P>
<P>
 Malli Star, who finished second behind Twice The Vice in the Del Mar Oaks, was 
third. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
