<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: JACOBSON WILL PLAY FOR NAVY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Blake Jacobson, a 6-foot-8 center at Crescenta Valley High, has accepted an 
appointment to the United States Naval Academy in Annapolis, Md., where he will 
play basketball. 
</P>
<P>
 Jacobson also took recruiting trips to the Air Force Academy and the U.S. 
Military Academy. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think (a military academy) can offer what no other school can offer," 
Jacobson said. "At a normal school you go four years and you play basketball 
and you are not even guaranteed a degree. At an academy, you get a great 
education and they pretty much guarantee you a degree, because they work with 
you so much. And then you have a job." 
</P>
<P>
 Jacobson averaged 8.9 points and 10.0 rebounds last year for the Falcons, who 
were the Southern Section Division I-AA runners-up. JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
