<TEXT>
<P>
 Starting defensive backs Davon Young and Eddie Lopez and defensive linemen 
Brandon McGee and Jaime Dongo of Sylmar High will miss Friday's Valley Pac-8 
Conference game against North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The players were suspended by the school for their roles in a fight last 
Friday during a game against Poly.McGee and Dongo will also miss the Spartans 
regular-season finale against Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 San Fernando High senior quarterback Larry Logan, who recently passed for 308 
yards in a game to break Anthony Davis' 25-year old school record, bruised his 
right shoulder earlier this week and may not start Friday against Taft. 
</P>
<P>
 Keijuan Douglas, who has started several games this season, is the backup. 
Golf 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Chen Olsen of Granada Hills had a two-day total of 151 this week to win 
the championship flight of the Women's Southern California Golf Assn. Stroke 
Tournament at Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Pearson of La Canada tied for third place at 156. Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Bruce Man Son Hing of Pasadena defeated Al Martinez of Hidden Hills, 7-5, 7-5, 
to win the singles championship of the Cabrini Open in Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Carluen of Los Angeles and Tom McDonald of Glendale defeated Jenia 
Karinov of Los Angeles and Doug Young of Burbank, 6-7, 7-5, 7-6, for the 
doubles championship. Roller Hockey 
