COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: DANA POINT; TOWN CENTER REVIVAL PLAN WILL GO TO PUBLIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A status report on the large-scale revitalization of the Town Center area will 
be given to residents Nov. 14. 
</P>
<P>
 At 6 p.m., the city staff will discuss plans for Town Center, the commercial 
area between Pacific Coast Highway and Del Prado Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will touch on the partnership between businesses and the city in 
deciding what the redesign should look like. 
</P>
<P>
 "One of the difficulties for Town Center is that a lot of the properties are 
smaller and fragmented," city planner Lance Schulte said. "The parking lots are 
not interrelated, and that means customers coming to shop here go from one 
parking lot to another." 
</P>
<P>
 Other subjects for discussion include creating business and public 
partnerships and establishing more resident workshops. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'll be dealing with traffic circulation issues and street designs and 
laying the groundwork for step-by-step public workshops in the future," Schulte 
said. 
