<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: AUTOS; DISNEYLAND WILL PLUG IN TO ELECTRIC VEHICLE INDUSTRY IN 
DECEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anaheim's Disneyland Hotel and Convention Center will be host to the electric 
car industry Dec. 3-7, when the International Electric Vehicle Symposium comes 
to town. 
</P>
<P>
 The biennial meeting is the 12th in a series that began in 1969 and alternates 
among European, Asia-Pacific and North American sites.The registration fee this 
year is $750 a person. 
</P>
<P>
 The next meeting in the United States is scheduled for 2004. 
</P>
<P>
 Though much of the symposium will be given over to technical panels on such 
topics as "Battery Modeling" and the "Technical Potential of Flywheel Storage," 
there will be an electric vehicle parade down Disneyland's Main Street and a 
public exposition at the hotel's convention center. 
</P>
<P>
 Scores of prototype electric cars and support equipment like recharging 
stations will be on display at the exposition on Saturday, Dec. 3, and Sunday, 
Dec. 4. Hours are 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. on Dec. 3 and noon until 4:30 on Dec. 4. 
Cost is $5 per person. 
</P>
<P>
 The parade will start at 1 p.m. on Dec. 1 and is open only to people who buy a 
general admission ticket to Disneyland that day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
