<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 'Megadealer' in Irvine: When Auto Age/Dealer Business magazine listed the 
nation's 100 largest "megadealers" earlier this month, it listed Webb 
Automotive Group as being in Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
 But the 26th-largest group in the country, with eight dealerships and $379.2 
million in 1993 sales, actually has considered Irvine its home for several 
years. 
</P>
<P>
 Owner Lewis Webb bought a trio of franchises in the Irvine Auto Center in 
October, 1989, and moved his favorite desk and chair from the Cerritos Auto 
Center to Irvine shortly thereafter. 
</P>
<P>
 But the company didn't make much of the move -- its corporate stationery still 
lists a Cerritos address. 
</P>
<P>
 In any event, Webb Automotive -- omitted from a Times Orange County listing 
earlier this month -- becomes the third of the nation's 100 largest megadealers 
to call Orange County home. 
</P>
<P>
 A fourth major operation, Fletcher Jones Management Group, has a big presence 
here, with affiliates Fletcher Jones Motor Cars -- the Newport Beach Mercedes 
Benz dealership -- and Ted Jones Ford in Buena Park. But the corporate 
headquarters remains in Las Vegas. 
</P>
