<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has appointed Heidi Holzinger and Jim Ashcraft to fill two 
seats on the city's Fine Arts and Cultural Affairs Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 Holzinger and Ashcraft will serve until Jan. 31, but are likely to be 
reappointed for three more years. 
</P>
<P>
 City Clerk Donna Velin said that the council normally reappoints committee and 
commission members who have served out unexpired terms. 
</P>
<P>
 The seven-member Fine Arts and Cultural Affairs Commission is responsible for 
holding the city's annual photo contest, an art show and other cultural events. 
The panel meets on the third Wednesday of each month at 7 p.m. in the council 
chambers. 
</P>
<P>
 One seat is still vacant, Velin said. Former commission members Kathi Volzke 
and Donna Overby have moved out of the city, and Althea Miller has been 
appointed director of Los Alamitos Television. 
</P>
<P>
 City policy prohibits residents from serving on two committees or commissions. 
</P>
<P>
 The other commission members are Leo Greene, Darleen Ortlieb, Donna McDonnell 
and student representative Michael Zilliox. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
